  "text": "For the nutrient content analysis, the seedlings were immersed in 1 mM EDTA for 1 h and then rinsed 6-8 times with ddH 2 O. Samples were dried at 75°C for 3 days and then were ground and digested in concentrated HNO 3 for 2-3 days. The samples were then boiled for approximately 1 h until completely digested. The contents of P, K, S, Fe, Mn, Cu, and Zn were determined using Inductively Coupled Plasma Atomic Emission Spectrometry (ICP-AES) as described by [CITATION_1] . Each experiment was repeated six times.",
